2017 WW08 Purley-FPGA Server SKX H0/LBG B1 Engineering Release Announcement (BKC #17)

\n \n \n

DEG Platform Integration Team

\n \n
\n

The DEG platform Integration team announces the release of 2017 WW08 Purley-FPGA Server SKX H0/LBG B1 Engineering release package for Intel internal use. The release is based on OS of\n \n RHEL7.3\n server. The auto-installer packages are available in the Artifactory server (both SH site and OR site). Any questions please contact Bei, Ling.

Status:\nNo fix. Details can be found 5345843 in HSD  


P&P Update:

1. Changed CPU from B0 to H0 for power and performance test from WW04.

2. Run NLB with Linux kernel 4.7.0, other tests are running with Linux Kernel 3.10.0

3. Runing NLB GBS mode 0 lpbk1 to exercise 2 sockets simultaneously for NLB loading power test.

4. Target for all test items are not ready, But OSS need target to generate report, so we just use WW43\'s data as target.

5. FPGA power workload: NLB

6. Core performance workloads: Mlc, Linpack, Stream.

WW08:

a) No regression issue found\xe3\x80\x82

b) For latest status of existing sightings, pls refer to the existing sightings table.

Key Workaround (detail guide is here)

\n\n

Please use PCIe Video card\ninstead of onboard BMC video due to known BMC issue

\n\n

 

Pedigree and Board\nJumper Settings: guide

\n\n\n\n

Note: Only mandatory and necessary optional rework\nis implemented by BKC team

Mandatory rework FPGA JTAG chain missing CPU1 TCK resistor

Mandatory rework to replace FPGA KR RX AC Caps

Mandatory rework add a pull down to RSMRST

Mandatory rework to update VR FW

CPLD updates to address IFWI issue with 2 SKX FPGA\nCPUs populated

Required\nCPLD updates to address reset and FSC issues
